</b></p>
<p><b>contravention of international human rights law.</b> </p>

<p><b>A/HRC/26/36/Add.2 
</b></p>
<p> <b>41 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Character of reply: no response 
</b></p>
<p><b>  </b><i>General observations: 
</i></p>
<p>61. The Special Rapporteur thanks the Government of Iraq for the responses to three 
</p>
<p>communications, while inviting the authorities to provide substantive replies to the other 
</p>
<p>two communications sent during the period under review. The Special Rapporteur will 
</p>
<p>follow with particular attention the developments regarding the investigations into the 
</p>
<p>attack on 1 September 2013 against the residents in Camp Ashraf and the level of their 
</p>
<p>compliance with international standards. He reiterates his deep concern about the 
</p>
<p>continuing reports on the very high number of executions and individuals at risk of 
</p>
<p>execution in Iraq, in violation of international human rights law, in particular of the most 
</p>
<p>serious crimes provision and the standards on fair trial and due process. Should these 
</p>
<p>allegations be corroborated, he calls upon the Government of Iraq to stay all executions and 
</p>
<p>commute without delay the death sentences. 
</p>
